Part of the reason Apex "had it's time" is that it isn't putting out content at the same pace as Fortnite
They made it very clear that they want to develop the game in such a way that is fair to the developers
Fortnite is putting out new content every 2 weeks or so, but people don't know or care about the human cost.  The overtime, the contractors.
Let this sink in.  Fortnite developers are working so long and so hard, that they can end up taking home bonuses worth 2 - 3 times their normal pay.

While it's fair to say that they're being well compensated, that level of sustained workload will burn people out in a matter of years, and then they're gone from the industry.  And that will just exacerbate the industry's inability to retain talent.

So, long story short, the AAA industry is heading for a bad time.  When the average career span for an industry is 5 (read that, FIVE) years, you're f*cked the moment mid - senior level staff are gone
I'll be damned if Fortnite doesn't know how to push my buttons...
